Preamble

This NeoCommons License ("License") is designed to foster technological progress by enabling broad access to technology for educational, research, and collaborative development. It establishes a framework for sharing knowledge and innovation freely while ensuring that commercial endeavors which benefit from the Technology contribute to its sustainability.

This License is a "source-available" or "shared-source" agreement. It is not an "open source" license as defined by the Open Source Initiative (OSI) because it includes specific obligations for Commercial Use. By using, modifying, or distributing the Technology, you ("Licensee") agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this document.

Section 1: Definitions

1.1. "Licensor" means the individual, entity, or entities that create or modify the Technology and make it available under this License.
1.2. "Technology" means the entirety or any part of the designs, systems, methods, or processes described in the Documentation.
1.3. "Documentation" means the schematics, design files, source code, textual descriptions, and any other explanatory materials explicitly released by the Licensor under this License.
1.4. "Product" means any hardware device, software program, system, or service whose design, operating principle, or core functionality is based, in whole or in part, on the knowledge, concepts, or solutions contained within the Documentation.
1.5. "Derivative Work" means: (a) any modification to the Documentation; and (b) any Product which, without access to the Documentation, could not have been created in a substantially similar form or with substantially similar functionality.
1.6. "Educational Use" means utilization by accredited educational institutions, their academic staff, and enrolled students exclusively for non-commercial teaching, scholarly research, or thesis work not primarily intended for commercial advantage or monetary compensation.
1.7. "Commercial Use" means any use, utilization, or distribution of the Technology or Documentation that does not qualify as Educational Use. This includes: (a) the sale, lease, or paid distribution of a Product; (b) providing a service for remuneration that incorporates or relies on the Product; (c) using the Product in marketing or advertising intended to generate revenue; and (d) distributing a Product as part of a business model.
1.8. "Net Revenue" means the total gross revenue from the sale, lease, or other paid provision of Products, less: (a) sales, use, or value-added taxes directly imposed on the transaction; (b) bona fide returns, credits, and allowances; and (c) outbound shipping, insurance, and customs duties directly incurred for delivering Products to customers.
1.9. "Affiliate" means any legal entity that directly or indirectly controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with the Licensee.
1.10. "Force Majeure" means any event beyond the reasonable control of a party, including acts of God, natural disasters, war, terrorism, government regulations, or pandemic.
1.11. "Substantial Modification" means any change to the Documentation that materially alters its core functionality, performance characteristics, or intended application.

Section 2: Grant of Rights

2.1. General Grant: The Licensor grants every Licensee a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive license to download, store, and use the Documentation for internal evaluation, testing, and analysis purposes.
2.2. Grant for Educational Use: For Licensees engaged in Educational Use, the Licensor grants a perpetual, worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, irrevocable license to: (a) create, use, and modify the Documentation; (b) create, use, modify, and distribute Products and Derivative Works; (c) publicly perform, display, and communicate the Documentation and Products, provided that attribution is given in accordance with Section 5.1.
2.3. Grant for Commercial Use: For Licensees engaged in Commercial Use, the Licensor grants a perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive, irrevocable (except as provided in Section 8) license to: (a) create, use, and modify the Documentation; (b) create, use, modify, and distribute Products and Derivative Works; (c) publicly perform, display, and communicate the Documentation and Products, provided that the Licensee complies with all obligations set forth in Section 3.

Section 3: Obligations for Commercial Use

3.1. Royalty Fee: A Licensee engaged in Commercial Use agrees to pay the Licensor a royalty fee equal to 1% of the Net Revenue generated from all Products. Payment instructions shall be provided by the Licensor or made publicly available at the Licensor's designated website or payment portal.
3.2. Reporting: The Licensee shall provide the Licensor with a written or electronic report within thirty (30) days after the end of each calendar quarter detailing Net Revenue and royalty fee calculation. Payment shall be remitted with the report.
3.3. Audit Rights: The Licensor or a designated independent certified accountant shall have the right, no more than once per calendar year and upon thirty (30) days' prior written notice, to audit the Licensee's financial records to verify royalty report accuracy. The audit shall be at the Licensor's expense unless a discrepancy of more than 5% in favor of the Licensor is discovered.
3.4. Revenue Threshold: Licensees with annual Net Revenue from Products below $10,000 USD (or equivalent) are exempt from royalty payments but must still provide quarterly reports. This threshold is adjusted annually for inflation using the US Consumer Price Index.
3.5. Late Payment: Overdue royalty payments shall accrue interest at 1.5% per month (18% per annum) from the due date until payment is received in full.
3.6. Currency and Exchange: All payments shall be made in US Dollars. For Net Revenue in other currencies, conversion shall use the XE.com exchange rate on the last business day of the reporting quarter.

Section 4: Copyleft and Transparency

4.1. Share-Alike: Any Derivative Work must be licensed under this NeoCommons License (version 1.0 or a later version).
4.2. Transparency: The Licensee must make all Documentation for any Derivative Work publicly available on an open-access platform in a reasonably accessible and documented format. This obligation does not apply to private, non-commercial use.
4.3. Version Compatibility: Derivative Works may be licensed under this version (1.0) or any later version of the NeoCommons License, provided the later version maintains substantially similar copyleft and transparency requirements.
4.4. Documentation Standards: All publicly released Documentation must include: (a) clear technical specifications; (b) installation or implementation instructions; (c) known limitations or safety considerations; and (d) version history with meaningful change descriptions.

Section 5: Attribution and Ethical Use

5.1. Attribution: The Licensee must include a clear and conspicuous notice in all copies of the Documentation and in public-facing materials which credits the original Licensor (e.g., "Based on technology from Artur Kujawa (Zigfi), licensed under the NeoCommons License v1.0") and provides a link to the full license text.
5.2. Ethical Use Limitations: The Technology, Products, or Derivative Works may not be used in any application primarily intended for: (a) Military applications, including weaponry, combat systems, or offensive cyberwarfare; (b) Systems of automated mass surveillance that infringe on fundamental human rights to privacy; (c) Systems designed for oppressive or coercive sociopolitical control.
5.3. Trademark and Branding: This License does not grant any rights to use the Licensor's trademarks, trade names, or branding.

Section 6: Anti-Circumvention and Patent Non-Aggression

6.1. Anti-Circumvention: Any action intended to create a Product for Commercial Use by leveraging the knowledge in the Documentation while attempting to evade royalty obligations shall be considered a material breach of this License.
6.2. Patent Non-Aggression: The Licensee agrees not to initiate any patent litigation against any other Licensee for using, developing, or improving the Technology under the terms of this License.

