7.1. Disclaimer of Warranty: THE TECHNOLOGY AND DOCUMENTATION ARE PROVIDED "AS IS," WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NONINFRINGEMENT.
7.2. Limitation of Liability: IN NO EVENT SHALL THE LICENSOR BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES, OR OTHER LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT, OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM, OUT OF, OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE TECHNOLOGY OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE TECHNOLOGY.

Section 8: Termination and Transition

8.1. The rights granted under this License will terminate automatically upon any breach by the Licensee of its terms and conditions.
8.2. Upon termination, the Licensee must immediately cease all use, modification, and distribution of the Technology, Documentation, and any Products or Derivative Works. Obligations accrued prior to termination shall survive termination.
8.3. Cure Period: If the breach is capable of cure, the Licensee shall have thirty (30) days from written notice of breach to remedy the violation. If cured within this period, the License shall remain in effect.
8.4. Force Majeure: Neither party shall be liable for any failure or delay due to Force Majeure events. If such events prevent performance for more than 90 consecutive days, either party may terminate this License upon written notice.

